<!DOCTYPE html>
<div id = "test-header" class="head-center container">
  <span id="logo-header"> <img style= 'width: 900px; margin-top: -70px' src='/images/Collab_logo.png'></span>

</div>

<div id = "what-we-do" class="head-center">
<h1> What We Do </h1>
<p class="what-info"> When creating comics, you'll need two key skills: good writing and artistic skills. Unfortunately, these skills are mutually exclusive: a great artist can be a terrible writer or the reverse is true: a great writer can be a terrible artist. This is where the idea of Collab-A-Comic comes in, to create a community where comic book writers and artists can find their ideal collaboration partner to work with. </p>
</div
>
<div id= "how-it-works" class="head-center">
  <h1> How it works </h1>
  <img id="howitworks" style = "width: 700px" src="/images/How_it_works.png">
</div>

<div id ="get-started" class="head-center">
  <h1> Getting Started </h1>
<p class="what-info"> Now that you have some familiarity with how the site works, let's get started by checking out the main sections of the site! </p>
<div class="row">
  <%= link_to artists_path do %>
  <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4">
    <div class="thumbnail main-wrapper">
      <i class="material-icons">brush</i>
      <div class="caption">
        <h3>Find an Artist</h3>
        <p>Search the site for an artist</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <%end%>
  <%= link_to writers_path do %>
  <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4">
    <div class="thumbnail main-wrapper2">
      <i class="material-icons" id="pen">edit</i>
      <div class="caption">
        <h3>Find a Writer</h3>
        <p>Search the site for a writer</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <% end %>
  <%= link_to publishedworks_path do %>
  <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4">
    <div class="thumbnail main-wrapper3">
      <i class="material-icons" id="book">import_contacts</i>
      <div class="caption">
        <h3>Read a Comic</h3>
        <p>Check out some of the comics created by the users from Collab-A-Comic!</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <%end %>
</div>

</html>
